    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0daa8b9b_dd972b27",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkJpegCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 258,
      "author": {
        "id": 5740
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-12-02T17:43:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "SkCodec doesn\u0027t work. You can\u0027t access protected members of another (or any from a static derived method) instance via the base class, so I had to make sure this was an SkJpegCodec instead of a SkCodec.\n\nI would\u0027ve loved to be able to avoid the codec temporary variable altogether and just assign to codecOut. I could\u0027ve casted *codecOut, but that is also kind of gross.",
      "parentUuid": "ede617fe_7f48eb2a",
      "revId": "3696e16dc69b4d397dff1a42689f3e2852f35eb9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ede617fe_bf06f3cc",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkPngCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 417,
      "author": {
        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-12-02T02:55:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Alternatively, you could change this to return SkColorSpace::MakeNamed(kSRGB).\n\nThen in the function below you could always setUnsupportedICC() if the colorspace is nullptr (no need for an out variable).  This would have the added effect (bonus?) of catching other failed attempts to specify SkColorSpaces.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 417,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 417,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "3696e16dc69b4d397dff1a42689f3e2852f35eb9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6db867f6_d86e0d6d",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkPngCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 417,
      "author": {
        "id": 5740
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-12-02T17:43:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It looks like PNG has some weird sRGB spec outside of ICC profiles on line 354. Then there\u0027s also that gamma info tag too on line 400. Unless you think the tool should not catch images with failed-to-parse ICC profiles that also happened to have those other PNG things (as back-ups or something)? Or am I missing something and a PNG can only have 1 of these things?",
      "parentUuid": "ede617fe_bf06f3cc",
      "revId": "3696e16dc69b4d397dff1a42689f3e2852f35eb9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6db867f6_5e8c2554",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkPngCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 417,
      "author": {
        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-12-04T21:27:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We will catch those...  We actually return MakeICC(), so the return value will be nullptr if we can\u0027t parse the profile.\n\nYou could argue that this behavior is strange...  Maybe we should keep looking for other color space tags after failing to parse the ICC profiles?  But there\u0027s not need to address that in this CL.",
      "parentUuid": "6db867f6_d86e0d6d",
      "revId": "3696e16dc69b4d397dff1a42689f3e2852f35eb9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
